---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Blog — Yasen Lilov" activePage="blog">

  <!-- Blog Header -->
  <section class="hero" style="padding-bottom: 20px;">
    <div class="container">
      <h1 style="font-size: 2.25rem;">Blog</h1>
      <p style="color: var(--text-secondary); margin-top: 8px;">Writing about analytics, data engineering, AI, and the tools that connect them.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Filters + Posts -->
  <section style="padding-top: 0; padding-bottom: 48px;">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="blog-filters">
        <button class="filter-btn active">All</button>
        <button class="filter-btn">How-To's</button>
        <button class="filter-btn">Thought Leadership</button>
        <button class="filter-btn">Google Analytics</button>
        <button class="filter-btn">Tracking Solutions</button>
        <button class="filter-btn">My Projects</button>
      </div>

      <div class="post-grid">

        <article class="post-card">
          <div class="post-card-meta">
            <span class="post-card-category">How-To</span>
            <span>Jun 2025</span>
          </div>
          <h3><a href="/blog/segment-implementation-deep-dive">Segment Implementation Deep-Dive [Part 1]: Architecture & Tracking Plan</a></h3>
          <p>A practical walkthrough of implementing Segment from scratch — covering architecture decisions, tracking plan design, and source configuration.</p>
          <div class="post-card-tags">
            <span class="tag">Segment</span>
            <span class="tag">CDP</span>
            <span class="tag">Architecture</span>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="post-card">
          <div class="post-card-meta">
            <span class="post-card-category">Thought Leadership</span>
            <span>Mar 2025</span>
          </div>
          <h3><a href="/blog/test-dont-guess">Test, Don't Guess: Data Analytics and Paid Ads for Faster PMF</a></h3>
          <p>How startups can use analytics and paid acquisition together to find product-market fit without burning cash on guesswork.</p>
          <div class="post-card-tags">
            <span class="tag">Analytics</span>
            <span class="tag">Paid Ads</span>
            <span class="tag">Startups</span>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="post-card">
          <div class="post-card-meta">
            <span class="post-card-category">Thought Leadership</span>
            <span>Mar 2025</span>
          </div>
          <h3><a href="/blog/ai-reshaping-marketing-analytics">How AI is Reshaping Digital Marketing Analytics</a></h3>
          <p>AI isn't replacing analysts — it's changing the questions we ask and the speed at which we can answer them.</p>
          <div class="post-card-tags">
            <span class="tag">AI</span>
            <span class="tag">Marketing</span>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="post-card">
          <div class="post-card-meta">
            <span class="post-card-category">Thought Leadership</span>
            <span>Mar 2025</span>
          </div>
          <h3><a href="/blog/ai-agents-service-businesses">Beyond Automation: The Rise of AI Agents in Service Businesses</a></h3>
          <p>AI agents are moving beyond chatbots. What happens when they can reason, plan, and execute multi-step business processes?</p>
          <div class="post-card-tags">
            <span class="tag">AI Agents</span>
            <span class="tag">Automation</span>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="post-card">
          <div class="post-card-meta">
            <span class="post-card-category">Thought Leadership</span>
            <span>Mar 2025</span>
          </div>
          <h3><a href="#">AI and Automation in Marketing: From Spreadsheets to Strategy</a></h3>
          <p>The shift from manual reporting to automated insight generation — and what it means for marketing teams.</p>
          <div class="post-card-tags">
            <span class="tag">AI</span>
            <span class="tag">Automation</span>
            <span class="tag">Marketing</span>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="post-card">
          <div class="post-card-meta">
            <span class="post-card-category">Thought Leadership</span>
            <span>Mar 2025</span>
          </div>
          <h3><a href="#">AI in Marketing and Analytics: It's Not Replacing Us, It's Empowering Us</a></h3>
          <p>Why the real opportunity in AI isn't cost-cutting — it's capability expansion for data professionals.</p>
          <div class="post-card-tags">
            <span class="tag">AI</span>
            <span class="tag">Analytics</span>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="post-card">
          <div class="post-card-meta">
            <span class="post-card-category">How-To</span>
            <span>Mar 2025</span>
          </div>
          <h3><a href="#">GA4 Measurement Protocol v2: Key Updates and Considerations</a></h3>
          <p>What's changed in the GA4 Measurement Protocol v2 and how to use it for server-side event collection.</p>
          <div class="post-card-tags">
            <span class="tag">GA4</span>
            <span class="tag">Measurement Protocol</span>
            <span class="tag">API</span>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="post-card">
          <div class="post-card-meta">
            <span class="post-card-category">How-To</span>
            <span>Mar 2025</span>
          </div>
          <h3><a href="/blog/ga4-server-side-tracking">GA4 Server-Side Tracking and the Future of Web Analytics</a></h3>
          <p>Server-side tagging is becoming essential. Here's how it works, when you need it, and how to set it up.</p>
          <div class="post-card-tags">
            <span class="tag">GA4</span>
            <span class="tag">Server-Side</span>
            <span class="tag">GTM</span>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="post-card">
          <div class="post-card-meta">
            <span class="post-card-category">How-To</span>
            <span>Oct 2023</span>
          </div>
          <h3><a href="/blog/ga4-data-redaction">GA4 Data Redaction: Clean PII in a Simple Way</a></h3>
          <p>A straightforward approach to keeping PII out of your GA4 data without overcomplicating your setup.</p>
          <div class="post-card-tags">
            <span class="tag">GA4</span>
            <span class="tag">Privacy</span>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="post-card">
          <div class="post-card-meta">
            <span class="post-card-category">How-To</span>
            <span>Aug 2023</span>
          </div>
          <h3><a href="#">Mastering GA4: The Essential Audit Guide</a></h3>
          <p>A comprehensive GA4 audit checklist — from property configuration to event tracking and data quality.</p>
          <div class="post-card-tags">
            <span class="tag">GA4</span>
            <span class="tag">Audit</span>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="post-card">
          <div class="post-card-meta">
            <span class="post-card-category">Tracking Solutions</span>
            <span>Dec 2022</span>
          </div>
          <h3><a href="#">What Does the GTM JS Script Actually Do?</a></h3>
          <p>A deep technical look at what happens when the Google Tag Manager JavaScript snippet loads on your page.</p>
          <div class="post-card-tags">
            <span class="tag">GTM</span>
            <span class="tag">JavaScript</span>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="post-card">
          <div class="post-card-meta">
            <span class="post-card-category">How-To</span>
            <span>Jan 2020</span>
          </div>
          <h3><a href="#">Data Normalization Made Easy with GTM</a></h3>
          <p>How to clean and normalize data layer values using GTM's built-in features before sending to analytics.</p>
          <div class="post-card-tags">
            <span class="tag">GTM</span>
            <span class="tag">Data Quality</span>
          </div>
        </article>

      </div>

      <div style="text-align: center; margin-top: 48px; color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 0.85rem;">
        Showing 12 of 38 posts &mdash; full pagination after content migration
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
